         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Ö of the left Ö [agrees] that Ö has from said [Herakles out of his house] an interest-bearing loan of [thirty eight drachmas] principal and that it is incumbent upon Ö to repay to Herakles the thirty-eight [drachmas of the loan] Ö and [the interest in the month of] Ö of the present third year of [Imperator Caesar Domitianus Augustus] Germanicus without Ö [and if he do not] return it as Ö (here the papyrus breaks off)</ab>
